---
/*
 * Refunds.astro — 7-day money-back refund policy.
 *
 * For apps that offer paid features. Aligns with Razorpay + Stripe defaults
 * and Indian consumer-protection norms.
 */
interface Props {
  appName: string
  appDomain: string
  contactEmail: string
  jurisdiction: string
  lastUpdated: string
}
const { appName, appDomain, contactEmail, jurisdiction, lastUpdated } = Astro.props
---

<article class="legal-page legal-refunds">
  <header class="legal-head">
    <p class="eyebrow"><a href="/">{appName}</a> / refunds</p>
    <h1>Refund Policy</h1>
    <p class="meta">Last updated · {lastUpdated} · {jurisdiction}</p>
  </header>

  <section class="legal-body">
    <p class="lede">
      A simple, no-questions-asked 7-day money-back window on any paid feature of
      <strong>{appName}</strong> ({appDomain}).
    </p>

    <h2>The 7-day window</h2>
    <p>
      If you've paid for a feature on {appName} and decide it's not for you, email
      <a href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`}>{contactEmail}</a> within 7 days of the charge
      and we'll refund the full amount. No questionnaire. No "what could we have done better"
      survey. We do read replies, but they're optional.
    </p>

    <h2>How to request</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>Email <a href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`}>{contactEmail}</a> with the subject "Refund".</li>
      <li>Include the email address you used to pay, and the rough date of the charge.</li>
      <li>That's it. We typically process within 2 business days.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>How long the money takes</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Razorpay (cards / UPI / netbanking)</strong> — 5–7 business days to land back in your account.</li>
      <li><strong>Stripe (cards)</strong> — 5–10 business days.</li>
      <li><strong>Other</strong> — case by case; we'll tell you when we issue the refund.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      The actual wait depends on your bank, not us. The refund leaves our payment
      processor within 2 business days of your request.
    </p>

    <h2>After 7 days</h2>
    <p>
      Refunds outside the 7-day window are at our discretion. If you've genuinely
      not used the feature, email and ask — we'll usually say yes. If you've used
      it heavily, we may decline. There's no "pro-rated refund on subscription"
      formula because {appName} doesn't run subscriptions (every paid feature is
      one-time or pay-as-you-go).
    </p>

    <h2>What we can't refund</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Third-party fees you paid to someone else (e.g. a domain registrar) even if you used {appName} to do it.</li>
      <li>Donations or "buy me a coffee" tips — those are gifts, not payments for service.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Disputes</h2>
    <p>
      If we can't agree, file a dispute with your card issuer or use the
      <a href="https://consumerhelpline.gov.in">National Consumer Helpline</a>
      (India) / equivalent in your jurisdiction. We always prefer to settle by
      email first — it's faster.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>Email: <a href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`}>{contactEmail}</a>. Jurisdiction: {jurisdiction}.</p>

    <slot />
  </section>
</article>

<style>
  .legal-page { max-width: 72ch; margin-inline: auto; padding-block: 2rem; }
  .legal-head { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule, #e5e5e5); padding-bottom: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .legal-head h1 { font-family: var(--font-display, Georgia, serif); font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem); margin: 0.25rem 0; }
  .eyebrow { font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--ink-mute, #666); margin: 0; }
  .eyebrow a { color: inherit; }
  .meta { font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--ink-mute, #666); margin-top: 0.5rem; }
  .legal-body h2 { font-family: var(--font-display, Georgia, serif); font-size: 1.5rem; margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .legal-body p, .legal-body li { line-height: 1.65; }
  .legal-body ul, .legal-body ol { padding-left: 1.25rem; }
  .lede { font-size: 1.125rem; color: color-mix(in oklab, var(--ink, #111) 90%, var(--paper, #fff)); }
</style>
